Alexandre is a social entrepreneur who has created and developed different social business in Africa for more than 13 years in different sectors: Education, Micro & Digital finance, Access to energy and digital.

Alexandre Coster is currently the Founder and CEO of Baobab+.

 Baobab+ was created to distribute innovative  products to improve and transform daily lives of African people in order to enable a sustainable economic development. Baobab+ is developing access to energy in West Africa (Senegal, Ivory Coast, Mali) and Madagascar,  through Pay-As-You-Go model to make the solar products accessible to all. Our ambition is to provide clean, affordable and reliable energy to people living off-grid by offering them quality products with adapted financial solutions. 
Baobab+ is also working on access to digital in providing to its clients  digital educative tablets.
Website: www.baobabplus.com 

Previously he created the first French Business School in Africa, ETICCA Dakar before being the group marketing director of Microcred group where he supported the development of new institutions and the digital transformation.

In 2017, Alexandre was selected as a Young Leader by AfricaFrance foundation and French Agency of Development (AFD).

Bertrand is an Associate Partner out of Dalberg Advisors’ Abidjan office. He is an experienced management consultant and development economist with expertise in private sector development, strategic planning, business development, partnership development, project management, and international economics.

Born and raised in Côte d'Ivoire, Bertrand built up a successful career as a management consultant with top-tier advisory firms in North America before choosing to advise leading African businesses and institutions as part of organizations such as the World Economic Forum and the Africa CEO Forum.

In his current role, Bertrand leverages his Audit & Conseil experience, management skills and passion for addressing Africa’s development challenges to support Dalberg’s growth in Africa as a key driver of the continent's economic and social progress, notably in the areas of private sector engagement, job creation and digital for development.
